<h2> <span class="mw-headline" id="Notes_for_Week_3:_2.2._Consumer_Surplus_and_the_Demand_Curve">Notes for Week 3: 2.2. Consumer Surplus and the Demand Curve</span></h2>
<p>Willingness to pay</p>
<p>Between price and demand curve=consumer surplus</p>
<p>Graphically, it is the area under the demand curve that is above the straight line representing y=price.</p>
<p><a href="/wiki/images/a/ab/Demand_Curve_and_Consumer_Surplus_1.jpg" class="image"><img alt="Demand Curve and Consumer Surplus 1.jpg" src="/wiki/images/a/ab/Demand_Curve_and_Consumer_Surplus_1.jpg" width="614" height="554" /></a></p>
<p>When the price falls, consumer surplus increases.  Likewise, when price increases, the consumer surplus goes away too.</p>
<p><a href="/wiki/images/7/74/Demand_Curve_and_Consumer_Surplus_2.jpg" class="image"><img alt="Demand Curve and Consumer Surplus 2.jpg" src="/wiki/images/7/74/Demand_Curve_and_Consumer_Surplus_2.jpg" width="600" height="531" /></a></p>
<p></p>

